  1. gcloud config set auth/impersonate_service_account (global, sticky)
  - Applies to all subsequent gcloud commands              
  - Must unset before switching to another SA          
  - Annoying for frequent switching                         

                                                 
  2. --impersonate-service-account= flag (per-command)
  - No global state to manage
  - Works on every gcloud command
  - Best for one-off commands, verbose for repeated use

  3. gcloud config configurations (named profiles)
  - Create named configs that each impersonate a different SA:
  gcloud config configurations create viewer
  gcloud config set auth/impersonate_service_account iam-vulnerable-viewer@$PROJECT_ID.iam.gserviceaccount.com
  gcloud config set project $PROJECT_ID

  gcloud config configurations create privesc1
  gcloud config set auth/impersonate_service_account privesc1-set-iam-policy@$PROJECT_ID.iam.gserviceaccount.com
  gcloud config set project $PROJECT_ID

  # Switch instantly between them
  gcloud config configurations activate viewer
  gcloud config configurations activate privesc1
  - This is the fastest way to switch between SAs

  4. Access token in environment variable (for API/curl)
  export TOKEN=$(gcloud auth print-access-token --impersonate-service-account=SA_EMAIL)
  curl -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" https://...

  5. Shell alias/function (wrapper)
  # Quick helper
  impersonate() { gcloud config set auth/impersonate_service_account "$1@$PROJECT_ID.iam.gserviceaccount.com"; }
  impersonate iam-vulnerable-viewer
  impersonate privesc1-set-iam-policy

  The named configurations (option 3) is the closest thing GCP has to "profile switching" like AWS. It's the cleanest for this project where you'd want a viewer config for enumeration and then switch to a specific privesc SA config for exploitation.




### Enumerate IAM (Discover Privesc Paths)

```bash
# List all service accounts - reveals the attacker SAs and high-priv target
gcloud iam service-accounts list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID --impersonate-service-account=$VIEWER_SA

# Get project IAM policy - shows who has what role
gcloud projects get-iam-policy $IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID \
  --flatten="bindings[].members" \
  --format="table(bindings.role, bindings.members)" \
  --impersonate-service-account=$VIEWER_SA

# List custom roles - reveals the vulnerable permissions granted to each SA
gcloud iam roles list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID --format="table(name, title)" --impersonate-service-account=$VIEWER_SA

# Inspect a specific custom role to see its permissions
gcloud iam roles describe ROLE_ID --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID --impersonate-service-account=$VIEWER_SA

# Check who can impersonate a specific SA (Token Creator bindings)
gcloud iam service-accounts get-iam-policy \
  SERVICE_ACCOUNT_EMAIL --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID \
  --impersonate-service-account=$VIEWER_SA

# Check who has actAs on the high-priv SA
gcloud iam service-accounts get-iam-policy \
  privesc-high-priv-sa@$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID.iam.gserviceaccount.com --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID \
  --impersonate-service-account=$VIEWER_SA
```

### Enumerate Resources by Service

```bash
# Compute Engine (Paths 10-16)
gcloud compute instances list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID
gcloud compute instance-templates list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID

# Cloud Functions (Paths 17-18)
gcloud functions list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID

# Cloud Run (Paths 19-22)
gcloud run services list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID
gcloud run jobs list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID

# Cloud Build (Paths 23-24)
gcloud builds triggers list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID

# Cloud Scheduler (Paths 25-26)
gcloud scheduler jobs list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID --location=us-central1

# Deployment Manager (Paths 27-28)
gcloud deployment-manager deployments list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID

# Composer (Paths 29-30)
gcloud composer environments list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID --locations=-

# Dataflow (Paths 31-32)
gcloud dataflow jobs list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID --region=us-central1

# Dataproc (Paths 33-34)
gcloud dataproc clusters list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID --region=-

# GKE (Paths 35-36)
gcloud container clusters list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID

# Notebooks (Paths 37-38)
gcloud notebooks instances list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID --location=-

# Workflows (Paths 40-41)
gcloud workflows list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID --location=us-central1

# Eventarc (Paths 42-43)
gcloud eventarc triggers list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID --location=-

# Workload Identity (Paths 44-45)
gcloud iam workload-identity-pools list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID --location=global

# Secrets & Storage (Lateral Paths)
gcloud secrets list --project=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID
gsutil ls -p $IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID
bq ls --project_id=$IAMVULN_PROJECT_ID
```